Helper: reads and transposes data table

read.tcsv = function(file, header=TRUE, sep=",", ...) {

  n = max(count.fields(file, sep=sep), na.rm=TRUE)
  x = readLines(file)

  .splitvar = function(x, sep, n) {
    var = unlist(strsplit(x, split=sep))
    length(var) = n
    return(var)
  }

  x = do.call(cbind, lapply(x, .splitvar, sep=sep, n=n))
  x = apply(x, 1, paste, collapse=sep) 
  out = read.csv(text=x, sep=sep, header=header)
  return(out)
}

Load and normalize original network

gold <- read.tcsv(goldFile, header=T)[1:alpha,]
gold <- na.omit(gold)
#head(raw)
# raw %>% ggplot(aes(x = ))

#Vertical shift
print(min(gold))
## [1] -4.6859
gold <- gold - min(gold)
#Should be 0
print(min(gold))
## [1] 0
#Scaling to unit length
gold <- gold / (max(gold) - min(gold))

#Normalized original
#head(raw)
print(min(gold))
## [1] 0
print(max(gold))
## [1] 1

Load a discretization output

discretized <- read.tcsv(method, header=TRUE)[1:alpha,]
## Warning in readLines(file): incomplete final line found on
## 'ADHD_Sub010_twin.csv'
#head(discretized)
rownames <- discretized[,1]
discretized <- na.omit(discretized[,-1])
discretized = discretized - min(discretized)
discretized = discretized / (max(discretized) - min(discretized))
#head(discretized)

Create a plottable data frame with all necessary information

plotter = function(raw, binary, node, time){
  raw = gold[[node]]
  binary = discretized[[node]]
  dfraw <- data.frame(time, raw)
  dfbin <- data.frame(time, binary)
  df <- data.frame(time, raw, binary)
  df <- df %>% gather(datatype, value, c(raw, binary))
  plot = ggplot(df, aes(x = time, y = value)) + geom_point(aes(color=datatype)) + geom_line(data=dfraw, aes(x=time, y=raw), color="blue") + geom_line(data=dfbin, aes(x=time, y=binary), color="red") + geom_area(data=dfraw, aes(x=time, y=raw), alpha=0.5, fill="blue") + geom_area(data=dfbin, aes(x=time, y=binary), alpha=0.5, fill="red") + ylim(0, 1) +  scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(1,alpha,1)) +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_text(size = rel(1.5)),
    legend.text = element_text(size = rel(1.5)),
    legend.title = element_blank(),
    axis.title = element_text(size = rel(2))
  )
  print(plot)
}
#Vectors for each node of original
